## Key Audit Checkpoints for ALN Accuracy

- Review all funding records and source documents for matching ALN assignment.[4]
- Check every transaction for valid, current ALN linkage, especially subawards.[2]
- Verify all financial and progress reports include the appropriate ALN with no errors.
- Confirm ALN presence, format, and consistency across the SEFA and audit schedules.[4]
- Log and report all ALN corrections; monitor for unresolved discrepancies before submission.

***

## Top Federal Penalties for ALN Non-Compliance

- Administrative penalties including grant termination or restructuring.[3]
- Recovery or withholding of awarded funds, future eligibility loss.[6][3]
- Suspension, debarment, or compliance corrective action mandates.[3]
- Civil/Criminal charges, fines, restitution or in severe fraud, prison time.[3]
- Public reporting of deficiencies and forced asset seizure in major violations.[3]

